title: Excitation functions of some (n,p) and (n,alpha) reactions from threshold to 16 MeV

x4freetext: Excitation functions of some (n,p) and (n,alpha)
reactions from threshold to 16 MeV

x4codes.hlp: Sofia, Inst. of Nuclear Res. and Nuclear Energy, Bulgaria
Institute for Nuclear Research (ATOMKI), Debrecen, Hungary

x4freetext: Kitahassaku 60, Midori-ku, Yokohama, Kanagawa

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Science and Engineering, Vol.129, p.164 (1998)

x4freetext: High-purity (Goodfellow) natural metal samples, disk-
shaped (19 mm diam.) with thickness between 0.25 and
1 mm, and rectangular (10x15 mm) shaped.
Absolute activity measurements.
Corrections were made for the following effects:
- true coincidence
- gamma-ray self-absorption
- dead time
- contribution of low-energy breakup neutrons to the
activation. Therefore the spectral shape of the
neutrons produced in the H-2(d,n)He-3 reaction was
determined by activation and pulse-height unfolding
methods.
Errors are from the following sources:
- counting statistics
- sample mass
- energy and fluence uncertainties
- decay constants
- effect of low-energy neutrons
- reference cross sections
- detector efficiency
HW.
OS. STATUS text corrected, changed to
4-digit year.
On. AUTHOR: .CS.M.BUCZKO -> Cs.M.Buczko
VS. REL-REF added to the article and the
Entry with incident neutron flux energy distribution
VS. DECAY-DATA corrected in 010.

x4freetext: Neutrons were produced by bombarding a thick TiT
target, in a scatter-free arrangement, with a
180 +- 5 keV deuteron beam. The neutron energy was
selected by the angular position of the sample with
respect to the deuteron beam axis.
Data are taken from table 3 of Nuclear Science and
Engineering, vol. 129, pp. 164-174 (1998).
OS.- Numerical values corrected.

x4freetext: Neutrons were produced by bombarding a 3 mm
thick Be target with 9.72 MeV deuterons.
The volume-averaged flux density spectra of the neu-
trons was determined via the multiple foil activation
technique and spectrum unfolding. The average energy
is 4.3 MeV ( J.Csikai, private communication).
Incident neutron flux energy distribution in
Subentry D0055002.

x4freetext: Incident

Sc and Ti foils with a set of Al,In,Fe,Ti,Au,Nb,Ni and
